{
  "texts": [
    "The designer first designs multiscale anchoring on each network of the feature sequence.",
    "Then, action classification and boundary regression are carried out according to the candidate proposals.",
    "The methods are mainly based on using sliding windows or anchor kernels to generate temporal action proposals.",
    "This section introduces anchor-based models in detail, from the earliest to the latest.",
    "Most previous methods have relied on hand-selected features with significant performance improvements."
  ]
}